    " \"cells\": [\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"# Fake News Detection\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"**NLP Project 9 of 100 · Beginner Text Classification**\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## Project Overview\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"This notebook builds a **binary classifier** to distinguish fake news articles from real ones. We use the GonzaloA/fake_news dataset from HuggingFace, comparing TF-IDF baselines against ModernBERT.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"**Models:** TF-IDF + MultinomialNB, LogReg, LinearSVC, SGD, RF, ModernBERT\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"**Metrics:** Accuracy, F1, Precision, Recall, ROC-AUC, Confusion Matrix\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## Learning Objectives\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"1. Build classifiers to detect fake news from article text\\n\",\n",
    "    \"2. Explore linguistic differences between fake and real news\\n\",\n",
    "    \"3. Compare TF-IDF and transformer approaches\\n\",\n",
    "    \"4. Understand limitations of text-only fake news detection\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"## Problem Statement\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"Given a news article (title + text), classify it as **fake** or **real**. Binary classification.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"## Why This Project Matters\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- Misinformation spreads faster than corrections on social media\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- Automated detection helps fact-checkers prioritize claims\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- Understanding fake news signals builds critical thinking about NLP limitations\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## Dataset Overview\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"| Property | Value |\\n\",\n",
    "    \"|----------|-------|\\n\",\n",
    "    \"| Source | HuggingFace `GonzaloA/fake_news` |\\n\",\n",
    "    \"| Classes | 2 (fake=0, real=1) |\\n\",\n",
    "    \"| Language | English |\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"## Dataset Source and License Notes\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"Fake news dataset commonly used in NLP research. Available on HuggingFace.\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## Environment Setup\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"import subprocess, sys, importlib\\n\",\n",
    "    \"for pkg in ['pandas','numpy','matplotlib','seaborn','scikit-learn','datasets','transformers','accelerate']:\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    try: importlib.import_module(pkg.replace('-','_'))\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    except ImportError: subprocess.check_call([sys.executable,'-m','pip','install','-q',pkg])\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print('Ready.')\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## Imports\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"import os,json,warnings,random\\n\",\n",
    "    \"import numpy as np, pandas as pd\\n\",\n",
    "    \"import matplotlib.pyplot as plt, seaborn as sns\\n\",\n",
    "    \"from sklearn.model_selection import train_test_split\\n\",\n",
    "    \"from sklearn.feature_extraction.text import TfidfVectorizer\\n\",\n",
    "    \"from sklearn.naive_bayes import MultinomialNB\\n\",\n",
    "    \"from sklearn.linear_model import LogisticRegression,SGDClassifier\\n\",\n",
    "    \"from sklearn.svm import LinearSVC\\n\",\n",
    "    \"from sklearn.ensemble import RandomForestClassifier\\n\",\n",
    "    \"from sklearn.calibration import CalibratedClassifierCV\\n\",\n",
    "    \"from sklearn.metrics import (accuracy_score,f1_score,classification_report,confusion_matrix,\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    roc_auc_score,RocCurveDisplay)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"warnings.filterwarnings('ignore')\\n\",\n",
    "    \"sns.set_style('whitegrid')\\n\",\n",
    "    \"%matplotlib inline\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print('Imports loaded.')\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## Configuration / Constants\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"SEED=42; MAX_ROWS=20000; TFIDF_MAX=20000; LABEL_NAMES=['fake','real']\\n\",\n",
    "    \"MODEL_NAME='answerdotai/ModernBERT-base'; MAX_LEN=256; BS=16; EPOCHS=2; LR=2e-5\\n\",\n",
    "    \"random.seed(SEED); np.random.seed(SEED)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"SAVE_DIR=os.path.dirname(os.path.abspath('__file__'))\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(f'Seed: {SEED}')\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## Dataset Download or Loading\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"from datasets import load_dataset\\n\",\n",
    "    \"try:\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    ds = load_dataset('GonzaloA/fake_news', split='train')\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    df = ds.to_pandas()\\n\",\n",
    "    \"except Exception:\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    try:\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        ds = load_dataset('fake_news', split='train')\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        df = ds.to_pandas()\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    except Exception:\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        ds = load_dataset('liar', split='train')\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        df = ds.to_pandas()\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        df['label'] = (df['label'] >= 3).astype(int)  # mostly-true/true=1, rest=0\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(f'Raw: {df.shape}, Columns: {list(df.columns)}')\\n\",\n",
    "    \"# Identify text and label columns\\n\",\n",
    "    \"if 'title' in df.columns and 'text' in df.columns:\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    df['combined'] = df['title'].fillna('') + ' ' + df['text'].fillna('')\\n\",\n",
    "    \"elif 'text' in df.columns:\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    df['combined'] = df['text'].fillna('')\\n\",\n",
    "    \"elif 'statement' in df.columns:\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    df['combined'] = df['statement'].fillna('')\\n\",\n",
    "    \"else:\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    df['combined'] = df.iloc[:,0].fillna('')\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"if 'label' not in df.columns:\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    df['label'] = df.iloc[:,-1]\\n\",\n",
    "    \"df = df[['combined','label']].rename(columns={'combined':'text'}).dropna().reset_index(drop=True)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"df['label'] = df['label'].astype(int)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"if len(df) > MAX_ROWS: df = df.sample(n=MAX_ROWS, random_state=SEED).reset_index(drop=True)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(f'Dataset: {df.shape}')\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(f'Label distribution:\\\\n{df[\\\"label\\\"].value_counts()}')\\n\",\n",
    "    \"df.head()\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## Data Validation Checks\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"print(f'Missing: {df.isnull().sum().sum()}')\\n\",\n",
    "    \"df = df[df['text'].str.strip().ne('')].reset_index(drop=True)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(f'Duplicates: {df.duplicated(subset=[\\\"text\\\"]).sum()}')\\n\",\n",
    "    \"df = df.drop_duplicates(subset=['text']).reset_index(drop=True)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(f'Final: {len(df)} rows')\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## Exploratory Data Analysis\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"df['text_len']=df['text'].str.len(); df['word_count']=df['text'].str.split().str.len()\\n\",\n",
    "    \"fig,axes=plt.subplots(1,2,figsize=(14,5))\\n\",\n",
    "    \"for lbl,c in [(0,'tomato'),(1,'steelblue')]:\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    s=df[df['label']==lbl]\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    axes[0].hist(s['word_count'],bins=50,alpha=0.5,color=c,label=LABEL_NAMES[lbl])\\n\",\n",
    "    \"axes[0].set_title('Word Count'); axes[0].legend()\\n\",\n",
    "    \"df['label'].value_counts().plot(kind='bar',ax=axes[1],color=['tomato','steelblue'])\\n\",\n",
    "    \"axes[1].set_xticklabels(LABEL_NAMES,rotation=0); axes[1].set_title('Class Distribution')\\n\",\n",
    "    \"plt.tight_layout(); plt.savefig(os.path.join(SAVE_DIR,'eda_distributions.png'),dpi=100); plt.show()\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## Target Analysis\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"Check balance. If roughly 50/50, accuracy is a valid primary metric.\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"print(f'Class balance: {df[\\\"label\\\"].value_counts(normalize=True).to_dict()}')\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## Train/Validation/Test Split Strategy\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"X=df['text'].values; y=df['label'].values\\n\",\n",
    "    \"X_train,X_test,y_train,y_test=train_test_split(X,y,test_size=0.2,random_state=SEED,stratify=y)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(f'Train: {len(X_train)}, Test: {len(X_test)}')\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## Preprocessing Strategy\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"TF-IDF captures stylistic differences between fake and real news.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"## Feature Engineering\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"tfidf=TfidfVectorizer(max_features=TFIDF_MAX,sublinear_tf=True,ngram_range=(1,2),min_df=3)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"X_tr=tfidf.fit_transform(X_train); X_te=tfidf.transform(X_test)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(f'TF-IDF: {X_tr.shape}')\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## Baseline Model: TF-IDF + MultinomialNB\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"bl=MultinomialNB(alpha=0.1); bl.fit(X_tr,y_train)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"yp=bl.predict(X_te); ypr=bl.predict_proba(X_te)[:,1]\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(f'Baseline Acc: {accuracy_score(y_test,yp):.4f}, F1: {f1_score(y_test,yp):.4f}')\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(classification_report(y_test,yp,target_names=LABEL_NAMES))\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## Traditional ML Classifier Comparison\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"> LazyPredict/FLAML not used for NLP.\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"clfs={'MultinomialNB':MultinomialNB(alpha=0.1),\\n\",\n",
    "    \"      'LogReg':LogisticRegression(max_iter=1000,random_state=SEED),\\n\",\n",
    "    \"      'LinearSVC':CalibratedClassifierCV(LinearSVC(max_iter=2000,random_state=SEED),cv=3),\\n\",\n",
    "    \"      'SGD':CalibratedClassifierCV(SGDClassifier(loss='hinge',random_state=SEED,max_iter=1000),cv=3),\\n\",\n",
    "    \"      'RF':RandomForestClassifier(n_estimators=200,random_state=SEED,n_jobs=-1)}\\n\",\n",
    "    \"results=[]; trained_models={}\\n\",\n",
    "    \"for name,clf in clfs.items():\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    clf.fit(X_tr,y_train); yp=clf.predict(X_te); ypr=clf.predict_proba(X_te)[:,1]\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    r={'Model':name,'Accuracy':accuracy_score(y_test,yp),'F1':f1_score(y_test,yp),\\n\",\n",
    "    \"       'ROC_AUC':roc_auc_score(y_test,ypr)}\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    results.append(r); trained_models[name]=(clf,yp,ypr)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    print(f\\\"{name:15s} | Acc={r['Accuracy']:.4f} | F1={r['F1']:.4f}\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"pd.DataFrame(results).sort_values('F1',ascending=False)\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## Why FLAML Is Not Used Here\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"> Not applicable for NLP.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"## Transformer Approach: ModernBERT Fine-Tuning\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"tr_res=None; y_pred_t=None; y_prob_t=None\\n\",\n",
    "    \"try:\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    import torch\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    from transformers import AutoTokenizer,AutoModelForSequenceClassification,Trainer,TrainingArguments\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    from datasets import Dataset\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    dev='cuda' if torch.cuda.is_available() else 'cpu'; torch.manual_seed(SEED)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    td=pd.DataFrame({'text':X_train,'label':y_train})\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    if len(td)>5000: td=td.sample(n=5000,random_state=SEED).reset_index(drop=True)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    tds=Dataset.from_pandas(td); eds=Dataset.from_pandas(pd.DataFrame({'text':X_test,'label':y_test}))\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    tok=AutoTokenizer.from_pretrained(MODEL_NAME)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    def tf(ex): return tok(ex['text'],truncation=True,padding='max_length',max_length=MAX_LEN)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    tds=tds.map(tf,batched=True); eds=eds.map(tf,batched=True)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    tds.set_format('torch',columns=['input_ids','attention_mask','label'])\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    eds.set_format('torch',columns=['input_ids','attention_mask','label'])\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    m=AutoModelForSequenceClassification.from_pretrained(MODEL_NAME,num_labels=2).to(dev)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    a=TrainingArguments(output_dir='./out',num_train_epochs=EPOCHS,per_device_train_batch_size=BS,\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        per_device_eval_batch_size=BS*2,warmup_ratio=0.1,weight_decay=0.01,learning_rate=LR,\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        eval_strategy='epoch',save_strategy='no',logging_steps=50,report_to='none',seed=SEED,fp16=torch.cuda.is_available())\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    def cm(ep): p=np.argmax(ep.predictions,axis=1); pr=torch.softmax(torch.tensor(ep.predictions),dim=1)[:,1].numpy(); return {'f1':f1_score(ep.label_ids,p),'roc_auc':roc_auc_score(ep.label_ids,pr)}\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    t=Trainer(model=m,args=a,train_dataset=tds,eval_dataset=eds,compute_metrics=cm)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    t.train(); po=t.predict(eds)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    y_pred_t=np.argmax(po.predictions,axis=1); y_prob_t=torch.softmax(torch.tensor(po.predictions),dim=1)[:,1].numpy()\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    tr_res={'Model':'ModernBERT','Accuracy':accuracy_score(y_test,y_pred_t),'F1':f1_score(y_test,y_pred_t),\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        'ROC_AUC':roc_auc_score(y_test,y_prob_t)}\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    print(f\\\"ModernBERT F1={tr_res['F1']:.4f}\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    del m,t; torch.cuda.empty_cache() if torch.cuda.is_available() else None\\n\",\n",
    "    \"except Exception as e: print(f'Transformer skipped: {e}')\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## Top 3 Model Selection\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"ar=results.copy()\\n\",\n",
    "    \"if tr_res: ar.append(tr_res)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"adf=pd.DataFrame(ar).sort_values('F1',ascending=False).reset_index(drop=True)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(adf.to_string(index=False,float_format='{:.4f}'.format))\\n\",\n",
    "    \"top3=adf.head(3)['Model'].tolist(); print(f'Top 3: {top3}')\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## Final Training and Evaluation of Top 3\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"t3d={}\\n\",\n",
    "    \"for n in top3:\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    if n in trained_models: t3d[n]={'yp':trained_models[n][1],'ypr':trained_models[n][2]}\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    elif n=='ModernBERT' and y_pred_t is not None: t3d[n]={'yp':y_pred_t,'ypr':y_prob_t}\\n\",\n",
    "    \"nc=len(t3d)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"fig,axes=plt.subplots(1,nc,figsize=(6*nc,5))\\n\",\n",
    "    \"if nc==1: axes=[axes]\\n\",\n",
    "    \"for i,(n,d) in enumerate(t3d.items()):\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    sns.heatmap(confusion_matrix(y_test,d['yp']),annot=True,fmt='d',cmap='Blues',\\n\",\n",
    "    \"                xticklabels=LABEL_NAMES,yticklabels=LABEL_NAMES,ax=axes[i])\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    axes[i].set_title(n)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"plt.tight_layout(); plt.savefig(os.path.join(SAVE_DIR,'confusion_matrices.png'),dpi=100); plt.show()\\n\",\n",
    "    \"for n,d in t3d.items(): print(f'\\\\n{n}'); print(classification_report(y_test,d['yp'],target_names=LABEL_NAMES))\"\n",
