    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## Interpretation and Business Insight\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"1. Fake news often uses sensationalized language that TF-IDF captures well.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"2. Writing style differences between fake and real news are strong signals.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"3. Text-only detection has limits — real fact-checking requires source verification.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"4. High accuracy on this dataset does not mean the model generalizes to all misinformation.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"## Limitations\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"1. Binary only — no credibility spectrum. 2. Dataset may have source-specific biases.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"3. Cannot verify factual claims, only detect stylistic patterns. 4. English only.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"## How to Improve\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"1. Add metadata (source, date, author). 2. Cross-reference with fact-checking databases.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"3. Multi-class credibility scoring. 4. Combine with claim verification.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"## Production Considerations\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- Pair with human fact-checkers. Style-based detection alone is insufficient.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"## Common Mistakes\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"1. Claiming style detection = fact verification. 2. Not testing on out-of-domain news.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"## Mini Challenge / Exercises\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"1. Use only titles (not full text) — how much does accuracy drop?\\n\",\n",
    "    \"2. Extract the top 20 TF-IDF features distinguishing fake from real.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"## Final Summary / Key Takeaways\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"1. Fake news detection from text is a binary NLP task with strong baselines.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"2. TF-IDF captures stylistic differences effectively.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"3. Text-only detection is a complement to, not replacement for, fact-checking.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"4. ModernBERT captures deeper semantic patterns in news articles.\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
